:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:130:"You read right, folks &#8211; one of our most-anticipated Content Sources has finally arrived on SlideDeck. Our code poets have...";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Jason";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4087:"<p>You read right, folks &#8211; one of our most-anticipated Content Sources has finally arrived on SlideDeck. Our code poets have pushed an update that will give you the ability to create Dynamic Source SlideDecks using your Pinterest images. Check out the Pinterest slider we created below!</p>\n<div class="slidedeck-link"><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/blog/stick-a-pin-in-it-pinterest-has-come-to-slidedeck/#SlideDeck-11039">SD Blog | Pinterest Announcement <small>[see the SlideDeck]</small></a></div>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Images sourced from the excellent Pinterest pinboard &#8220;<a href="http://pinterest.com/cfikare/architecture-bridges/" target="_blank">Architecture-Bridges</a>&#8220;</em></p>\n<p>Oh, you&#8217;re still here? Well then, allow me to give you a quick guide as to what&#8217;s in the update.</p>\n<h3>30 Seconds for Pinterest Perfection</h3>\n<p>It really couldn&#8217;t be much simpler &#8211; to get started, all you need to do is select Pinterest as a content source either from the Manage screen, or in the Dynamic Source editor screen.</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10930" title="pinterest_modal" src="http://assets-slidedeck2.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/pinterest_modal.jpg?9d7bd4" alt="" width="520" height="256" /></p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;re on the Dynamic Source Editor screen, simply paste in the URL of a user&#8217;s profile page, or the link to the actual board, and hit &#8220;Apply&#8221;.</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10929" title="pinterest_flyout" src="http://assets-slidedeck2.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/pinterest_flyout.jpg?9d7bd4" alt="" width="520" height="320" /></p>\n<p>And boom, you&#8217;re done!</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10933" title="pinterest_slider" src="http://assets-slidedeck2.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/pinterest_slider.jpg?9d7bd4" alt="" width="520" height="456" /></p>\n<p>Actually, that&#8217;s a lie &#8211; you&#8217;ll of course want to tweak your Lens&#8217; appearance and playback settings <em>just so</em> to create the perfect Pinterest slider. After all, that&#8217;s why everyone knows you&#8217;re the go-to style maven, right?</p>\n<p>This feature isn&#8217;t built on the official Pinterest API, rather the result of a little tinkering on our part, so we&#8217;ll definitely be looking to fill out this Content Source with more robust capabilities. As it stands, though, we just can&#8217;t get enough of creating awesome Pinterest sliders!</p>\n<p><strong>What do you think of the new Content Source? Have any cool ideas for using it? Share with us in the comments!</strong></p>\n<br/><br/><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/pricing/?utm_source=feed_ad&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=sd_blog"><img src="//s3.amazonaws.com/assets-slidedeck2/wp-content/themes/slidedeck2/images/sd-rss.jpg?9d7bd4" alt="Easily create AWESOME WordPress sliders - Get SlideDeck" style="display:block;border:none;"/></a><div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=v2mPa2HOBoA:i99qThr5Joo:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=v2mPa2HOBoA:i99qThr5Joo:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=v2mPa2HOBoA:i99qThr5Joo:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a h