ngs a bunch of awesome new features <a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/blog/new-2-1-screenshots-a-content-source-and-important-announcements/">that we&#8217;ve talked about previously</a>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Multiple content sources</strong> &#8211; now you can mix together multiple content sources in one SlideDeck</li>\n<li><strong>Custom content SlideDecks</strong> &#8211; Curate your SlideDeck slide-by-slide, with different layouts on each</li>\n<li><strong>HTML slides</strong> &#8211; SlideDeck now accepts your HTML &#8211; embed forms, build complex layouts, and more</li>\n<li><strong>500px content source support</strong> &#8211; Now you can create awesome slideshows using your images hosted on 500px</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Current SlideDeck 2 users can update their plugin from within WordPress. <span style="background-color: yellow;">Remember to install your Addons after you&#8217;ve updated the plugin, to gain access to all the new functions!</span></p>\n<p>We&#8217;d also like to say a huge thanks to the folks over at TechCrunch <a href="http://techcrunch.com/2012/06/18/slidedeck-2-1/" target="_blank">for their writeup</a>.</p>\n<p>Go ahead, try it out, and be sure to <a href="http://dtelepathy.zendesk.com/forums/20554402-faq" target="_blank">check out the FAQs</a>, or <a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/contact-us/">contact us</a> if you have any questions. <strong>If you don&#8217;t own SlideDeck yet, there&#8217;s never been a better time &#8211; <a href="http://slidedeck.com/pricing">buy SlideDeck today</a>.</strong></p>\n<p>We&#8217;re excited to see what you guys do with it!</p>\n<br/><br/><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/pricing/?utm_source=feed_ad&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=sd_blog"><img src="//s3.amazonaws.com/assets-slidedeck2/wp-content/themes/slidedeck2/images/sd-rss.jpg?9d7bd4" alt="Easily create AWESOME WordPress sliders - Get SlideDeck" style="display:block;border:none;"/></a><div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slid