l interfaces in order to foster a sense of familiarity in users. Common examples of this include paper textures on notepad applications, thread stitching in interface borders, and transparent glass surfaces for application covers.</p>\n<p>In user experience design, digital skeuomorphism holds great potential for bringing rich emotional experiences to digital devices, which are otherwise impersonal. If you’re looking to leverage digital skeuomorphism into your next design, take inspiration from the following fifty examples.</p>\n<h3>Books, Paper, and Stationery</h3>\n<p><a href="http://dribbble.com/shots/437952-Folded-paper-friend"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-8797" title="01_paper" src="http://www.dtelepathy.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/01_paper.png" alt="" width="580" height="320" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://creattica.com/mobile/invoicer/82856"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-8798" title="02_paper" src="http://www.dtelepathy.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/02_paper.png" alt="" width="580" height="320" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://cartographer-app.com/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-8799" title="03_paper" src="http://www.dtelepathy.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/03_paper.png" alt="" width="580" height="320" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://kidoodleapps.com/products/pirate-scribblebeards-treasure/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-8800" title="04_paper" src="http://www.dtelepathy.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/04_paper.png" alt="" width="580" height="320" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://sophiestication.com/onthisday/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-8801" title="05_paper" src="http://www.dtelepathy.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/05_paper.png" alt="" width="580" height="320" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.apple.com/iphone/built-in-apps/reminders.html"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-8802" title="06_paper" src="http://www.dtelepathy.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/06_paper.png" alt="" width="580" height="3