(56, 1, '2012-07-21 20:09:56', '2012-07-21 20:09:56', '<strong>Mission Statement\n</strong>\n\nThe Galvin Education &amp; Resource Center for Families is a non-profit organization founded in 1997,  committed to assisting families in their quest to help their children achieve their maximum potential by providing innovative educational and state-of-the-art intervention programs.\nGERCF\n\nInitial funding: Monies left from the original Listening Center in Cleveland (the first in the United States) helped fund the start up of this non-profit. Those funds were used to begin to train therapists to administer emerging listening interventions. As a result, The Listening Center of Ohio (TLC) now offers 4 options for parents interested in using listening protocols to remediate specific auditory processing disruptions impacting sound sensitivity , listening, attention and communication skills among others.inclinicParents, professionals and children are served by existing and newly developed programs and interventions offered throughout the year.\n\nThe Creative Learning Academy Preschool, founded in June, 2012.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', '', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-autosave', '', '', '2012-07-21 20:09:56', '2012-07-21 20:09:56', '', 7, 'http://74.52.18.28/~gercf/?p=56', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
